data.description: There is room for everyone  in this expansive home located on a cul-de-sac in one of Mt. Kisco's most sought after neighborhoods. With 6 large bedrooms, 5 full baths, 2 kitchens, a full walkout basement. You'll have plenty of options  for a home office, playroom, gym & still have a place to call your own. The original ranch was doubled in size in 2005 w/ the addition of the entire second floor. Then also adding an entire new heating system, full size stand up attic, new roof & changing it into a Colonial. Close to gorgeous Leonard Park, many restaurants & shops. A 3 min car ride to Mt. Kisco Train Station & convenient to I-684, & the Saw Mill Pkway. This home is in the Bedford School District w/West Patent Elementary School. This extended colonial has hardwood floors throughout the home, the main living room is anchored by built-ins & a wood burning fire place. The main eat-in kitchen has recently been updated & allows for a nice flow to the dining area as well as the deck, both of which overlook the private backyard that is bordered by NY State Land. A panoramic sunroom makes for a cozy spot to take in the fall foliage or watch the snow fall this winter. 3 large bedrooms are on the main floor with a Primary Bedroom & Primary Bath being a first floor option as well. Upstairs has several options for personalizing the house to suit your needs. An additional kitchen is onsite (with approval), a den/living room with pocket doors & an adjoining corner room makes for a great home office, play area/nursery, or guest quarters. A full hallway bath & 3 more bedrooms are upstairs, one a second Primary Bedroom w it's own Bath. Storage is abundant in this house w/ a unfinished room off the upstairs primary bedroom ripe for a grand closet. A massive attic & basement storage allow to pack it all. The basement houses a Recreation area, full bath & a finished living area w/ sliders & walkout to a covered patio. Set up the basketball hoop in the driveway, let the children ride their bikes in the cul-de-sac & don't sacrifice any conveniences , all while enjoying nature from your backyard.
